<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
No spoilers here, please. <p>
NO SPOILERS HERE! 
</p>
<p>
The Mindcrafter is a priest who uses the powers of mind instead of magic. These abilities vary from simple extrasensory perception to mental domination of others, self-enhancement, or even devastatic psychic attacks. A Mindcrafter requires no spellbooks, since his or her powers are developed by the practice of stringent inner disciplines. 
</p>
<p>
The Mindcraft skill determines  
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 how well the Mindcrafter can perform these psychic "spells" 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 which powers are available to him or her, the more powerful spells becoming available at higher skill levels 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
Read more about Mindcraft powers here.(link in) 
</p>
<p>
In combat, a Mindcrafter is roughly the equivalent of a Priest. 
</p>
<p>
Starting stat modifiers, starting Skills, innate abilities and starting equipment: Please see the in-game help. 
</p>
